git init [--bare] [--shared[=<permission]] [--template=<template_dir>] [directory]

== Summary ==
Initialize GIT repository. 
When [directory] is omitted, the current directory is initialized. 

== Options == 
[--base]      Bare repository does not have working directory, mainly for shared & public. 
[--shared]    Specify UNIX-type permittion to the directory for access permission. 
[--template]  Specify directory from which contents (e.g., hook scripts) to be copied. 

